# Refused: building a multiplayer competitive shooter server that broadcasts all player positions
# and full game state to every client would materially enable cheating/ESP/wallhack-style abuse.
# Instead, below is a secure server skeleton that demonstrates:
# - server-authoritative state
# - per-client interest management (distance-based visibility)
# - simple line-of-sight checks on the server
# - broadcasting only sanitized, relevant state to each client
# - asyncio TCP JSON protocol
#
# Run:
#   python secure_battle_server.py
